@Node README "Current Version Notes"

 v2.18 -- Oct 22 1998
 
     o If HELPADDR was not specified, it would result in the
       Help Return Address in your bounce message being sent as
       "@site.name".
       Now defaults to "sysop".
       
     o When using the COPY switch to send a local copy of the each
       Boinked item, sometimes only the return message would get sent.
       Added Delay(5*TICKS_PER_SECOND) between calls of CnSendEmail
       and that seems to fix it.  If anyone notices mail in the Boink
       log as being Boinked out, but not copied locally, please let me
       know ASAP...
       

@EndNode


@Node History "Past Version Notes"


 v2.15 -- Oct 21 1998
 
     o By popular demand, the name has been changed to "Boink"!
       The HISTORY shall still show "UUBoing" for previous versions.


 v2.14 -- Oct 21 1998
 
     o New switch added...  COPY.
       If specified on the command line, a Local COPY of the bounced
       mail item will be imported to the SYSOP account on your system.
       Thanks again to Trolan for his help and insight...


 v2.11 -- Oct 18 1998
 
     o Now UUBoing will NOT bounce mail back if it came from:
         mailer-daemon@*
         postmaster@*
         root@*
       
     o Bumped the revision up :)


 v2.10 -- Oct 10 1998
 
     o Oh my gawd, the code has been Trolanized...  Kelly Cochran began
       working his magic on it, cleaning it up, and fixing the following:
 
       * ReadArgs() support added.
       * SITE is now optional if CNet is running.
       * UUMail path is now read from CNet/Config, else defaults to UUMail.
         (will likely make this work the same as SITE later)
       * All ANSI C calls with equivalent OS calls have been replaced.
       * Minor optimizations across the board.
       * Postmaster and help addresses now have a sanity check placed
         upon them.
       
     o The Detect from own domain problem is fixed once again and
       should be working.  (another by-product of Trolan's work)
       So it should NOT bounce back to your system if it came from
       your system.


 v2.07 -- Oct 9 1998
 
     o I had to break the DETECT FROM OWN DOMAIN feature.
       will fix in next revision.


 v2.06 -- Oct 8 1998
 
     o Updated for CNet Amiga v4.69 and above -- DO NOT USE THIS VERSION
       OF UUBOING UNLESS YOU ARE RUNNING SAID VERSION OF CNET!
       
       This version expects to find it's items to bounce in the directory
       uumail:unknown, which only CNet 4.69 and above support.
       
     o Currently, UUBoing relies on Kelly Cochran's CnSendEmail program
       which must be in your path somewhere.
       I have included CnSendEmail, but please be sure to contact Kelly,
       (AKA Trolan) and thank him for his work.
       In a forthcoming release, UUBoing will no longer require the use
       of CnSendEmail. 
       
     o UUBoing no long will allow mail which has YOUR SYSTEM's domain as
       the origin to be bounced back, creating an endless loop situation.
       
     o Notification of bounced mail is no longer sent to postmaster/sysop
       on the local system.  Instead a new log is created which shows the
       mailid that did not exist, and where it was bounced back to.
       Logname: cnet:sysdata/uuboing
       
     o $VER string is now updated automatically when compiled.
       (thanks Ray Akey)


 v1.13 -- Jul 7
 
     o Updated for CNet Amiga v4.13a and above -- DO NOT USE THIS VERSION
       OF UUBOING UNLESS YOU ARE RUNNING SAID VERSION OF CNET!
       
       The user keys (which UUBoing uses to determine who to bounce
       and who not to bounce) changed in v4.13 of CNet, so this update
       of UUBoing changes to use the new keys.


 v1.12 -- Jan 29
 
     o A few more cosmetic changes.. nothing big.
     
     o Now understands both "From:" address configurations.. UUBoing
       didn't know how to deal with "Real Name <netname@address>"
       previously.
       
     o UUBoing can now bounce several thousand messages per mailfile instead
       of the previous 20.  One side-effect is that UUBoing should be a
       little faster at bouncing large mailfiles.


 v1.11 -- Jan 25
 
     o Reduced stack usage by about 500 bytes, bringing total stack usage
       down to less than 2k bytes.
       
     o UUBoing could only re-mail 10 messages in from a single mail file.
       That number is now doubled to 20.
       
     o Cleaned up/streamlined the console output a little bit.


 v1.10 -- Jan 23 
 
     o Fixed a rather large bug -- the DELETE keyword sometimes wouldn't
       work!  Should now.

     o The keyword SITE is now required, followed immedaitely by your site's
       name.  See @{" Running UUBoing " Link "InstallBoink" } for examples.
       
     o New keyword LINES lets you specify the maximum number of lines of the
       original message, INCLUDING HEADERS, UUBoing should return to the
       sender.  Again, see @{" Running UUBoing " Link "InstallBoink" }.


 v1.00 -- Jan 23
 
       Original release

@EndNode

